<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>RADIATOR/COOLING SYSTEM SERVICE MANUAL - PROSTAR&#8482; - COOLING PACKAGE COMPONENTS - TRANSMISSION OIL
        COOLER
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="Remove and Install" graphiccount="3">
        <title>TRANSMISSION OIL COOLER</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Transmission Oil Cooler - Removal</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The grille must be removed from the hood to gain access to the transmission oil cooler.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f1202114" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg12/G1202114.webp" type="webp" scalefitwidth="312px" scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 19. Grille</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. HOOD ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. TAB INSERTS</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. GRILLE</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. GRILLE MOUNT SCREWS</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove four mount screws from the lower portion of the grille.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To remove the grille, lift the grille out to release the tabs from the tab inserts.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Unlatch and open the hood.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Release latches and lower the tilt-away bumper.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1202115" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg12/G1202115.webp" type="webp" scalefitwidth="312px" scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 20. Transmission Oil Cooler Hoses</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. TRANSMISSION OIL COOLER TUBE BRACKET BOLT</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. TRANSMISSION OIL COOLER TUBE BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. TRANSMISSION OIL COOLER TUBES</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. TRANSMISSION OIL COOLER HOSES</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place a suitable container under the transmission oil cooler hoses to catch any oil from
                    the system.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect two transmission oil cooler hoses from the transmission oil cooler tubes.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Cap ends of the transmission oil cooler tubes and transmission oil cooler hoses.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the transmission oil cooler tube bracket bolt.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1202116" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg12/G1202116.webp" type="webp" scalefitwidth="312px" scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 21. Transmission Oil Cooler</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. RADIATOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. TOP MOUNT BOLTS</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. TRANSMISSION OIL COOLER MOUNT BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. TRANSMISSION OIL COOLER</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. BOTTOM MOUNT BOLTS</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove two bottom mount bolts and two top mount bolts from the transmission oil
                    cooler.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the transmission oil cooler by sliding the transmission oil cooler down and
                    rotating out of the chassis.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Transmission Oil Cooler - Installation</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Inspect the transmission oil cooler prior to installation for damage.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the transmission oil cooler on the front of the radiator by sliding the
                    transmission oil cooler up from the bottom of the vehicle and rotating into the mounting position.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install two top mount bolts and two bottom mount bolts on the transmission oil cooler (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1202116">Figure 21, Items 2 and 5</hotlnk>). Torque bolts to 33 to 40 lbf-ft (45 to
                    54 N&#8226;m).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the oil cooler tube bracket bolt (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1202115">Figure 20, Item 1</hotlnk>). Torque bolt to 33 to 40 lbf-ft (45 to 54 N&#8226;m).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the capped ends from the transmission oil cooler tubes and transmission oil
                    cooler hoses.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect two transmission oil cooler hoses to the transmission oil cooler tubes (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1202115">Figure 20, Items 3 and 4</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Close bumper and secure latches.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Prior to installing the grille, inspect the mounting tabs on the upper surface of the grille
                        and the tab inserts on the hood. Insure that all tabs and tab inserts are functional and in
                        place.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align grille tabs with the hood tab insert holes (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1202114">Figure 19, Item 2</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With the palm of your hand, press the grille at all six tab insert locations to seat
                    grille onto the hood.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install four mount screws in bottom of grille (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1202114">Figure 19, Item 4</hotlnk>). Torque screws to 4 to 5 lbf-ft (6 to 7 N&#8226;m).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check and fill transmission fluid as needed. Refer to Transmission Operator's Manual for
                    fluid type and filling instructions.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
